Class DTLZ6

jeco.core.problem.Problem<Variable<Double>>
jeco.core.benchmarks.dtlz.DTLZ
jeco.core.benchmarks.dtlz.DTLZ6
public class DTLZ6 extends DTLZ
DTLZ6 problem This class represents the DTLZ6 problem. It is a subclass of the DTLZ class. The DTLZ6 problem has the following properties: - Number of variables: 12 - Number of objectives: 3 - Bounds for variables: [0, 1] - Type of variables: real - Pareto front: convex - Pareto set: convex The DTLZ6 problem is defined as follows: - Minimize f1, f2, f3 - f1 = 1 + g - f2 = 1 + g - f3 = 1 + g - g = sum_{i=numberOfVariables-k+1}^{numberOfVariables} (x_i - 0.5)^2 - k = numberOfVariables - numberOfObjectives + 1 - x_i in [0, 1] - i = 1, 2, ..., numberOfVariables
